# Built by dot-update.d/ollama as the `offload` model - `ollama run offload`.
#
# Tuned for fast, low-stakes tasks handed down from Claude to save cost:
# formatting, summarizing, extracting data, boilerplate, straightforward
# lookups. Not for code review or anything reasoning-heavy - that stays
# with Claude.
#
# This box is CPU-only (i7-7500U, 2c/4t, no GPU) - its comparative
# advantage over htpc's `offload` (profiles/htpc/ollama/Modelfile.offload)
# is availability, not quality: no network dependency, works when htpc or
# the LAN is down. Built FROM the 3b model, not the 7b one also pulled
# here, and num_ctx is kept small - both trade quality for staying fast on
# weak CPU. Reach for htpc's llm.home for anything worth the wait; use this
# one when local-and-instant matters more than local-and-good.
#
# This file is the knob-turning playground. Copy it (Modelfile.<name>) and
# change FROM / PARAMETER / SYSTEM to build other tuned variants, then:
#   ollama create <name> -f ollama/Modelfile.<name>
# No re-download - relayering an already-pulled base is instant, so it's
# cheap to try a variant, run a few prompts, and throw it away.
#
# Knobs worth playing with:
#   temperature    0.0-1.0+   lower = more deterministic/focused, higher = more varied
#   top_p          0.0-1.0    nucleus sampling cutoff - lower narrows word choice
#   top_k          int        caps candidate tokens per step - lower = more conservative
#   num_ctx        tokens     context window - higher costs more RAM + slower per-token
#   repeat_penalty float      >1.0 discourages repeating the same phrasing
#   num_predict    tokens     hard cap on response length
#
# Full parameter reference: https://github.com/ollama/ollama/blob/main/docs/modelfile.md

FROM llama3.2:3b

PARAMETER temperature 0.3
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_ctx 2048
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

SYSTEM """
You are a fast local assistant handling small, well-defined tasks offloaded
from a larger assistant to save cost - formatting, summarizing, extracting
data, boilerplate generation, straightforward lookups. Answer directly and
concisely. If a task needs deep reasoning, broad context, or a judgment call
you're not confident in, say so plainly instead of guessing.
"""
